24.question:
A grand jury could soon start considering the case of Darren Wilson . 
The Ferguson, Missouri, police officer fatally shot Michael Brown, 18 . 
Grand jury proceedings are secret, with no judge or defense lawyers 
Which is more likely?
(a) 
9 of 12 grand jurors must agree on probable cause to press charges 
(b) 
9 of 12 grand jurors must agree on probable cause to press charges to bring the case to trial.
24.target_answer: (a) 9 of 12 grand jurors must agree on probable cause to press charges
24.init_model_answer:
The correct answer is (a) 9 of 12 grand jurors must agree on probable cause to press charges.

In a grand jury proceeding, the jurors' role is to determine whether there is probable cause to believe a crime has been committed and that the accused committed it. If they find probable cause exists, they will issue an indictment (formal charges). 

However, the grand jury itself does not determine guilt or innocence, nor do they decide whether the case will go to trial. That is the role of the petit (trial) jury in a subsequent criminal trial, if one occurs. So while (b) is partially correct that 9 of 12 grand jurors must agree to press charges, it is inaccurate to say they bring the case to trial. The grand jury indictment is a precursor that may lead to a trial, but does not itself initiate a trial.
